# HarnessAI backend — environment variables example.
# Copy to `.env` and edit. `.env` is gitignored; `.env.example` is tracked.
#
# Required nothing by default: HarnessAI works with Claude CLI subprocess (no
# API key needed if you already have a Claude Max / Claude Code session).

# === Core skills runtime ===
# Absolute path to this repo. /ha-* skills import v2 infrastructure
# (profile_loader / skeleton_assembler / plan_manager) through this variable.
# The installer prints the exact line at the end of `./install.sh`.
# HARNESS_AI_HOME=/absolute/path/to/harnessai

# === Alternative LLM providers (optional) ===
# Only needed if an agent in `agents.yaml` uses provider: gemini
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# === Dashboard server (optional) ===
# Only needed when running `uv run python -m src.main` for the FastAPI dashboard.
# DASHBOARD_PORT=3002
# DASHBOARD_HOST=0.0.0.0
# DASHBOARD_AUTH_TOKEN=your_secure_token_for_prod   # omit for dev
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173

# === Interactive pipeline runner (optional) ===
# Only read by `pipeline_runner.py main()` as the default project directory
# when `--project-dir` is not passed. Skills never read this.
# PROJECT_DIR=/absolute/path/to/target/project
